1 AN ACT relating to relating to motor vehicle licensing and registration procedures.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 186.020 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Before the owner of a motor vehicle may operate it or permit its operation upon a
5 highway, the owner shall apply for registration in accordance with administrative
6 regulations promulgated by the cabinet, except that a person who purchases a motor
7 vehicle, or brings a motor vehicle into the Commonwealth from another state shall
8 make application for registration within fifteen (15) days. The bill of sale or
9 assigned title must be in the motor vehicle during this fifteen (15) day period. If the
10 owner of a motor vehicle is an individual and resides in the Commonwealth, the
11 motor vehicle shall be registered with the county clerk of the county in which he or
12 she resides. If the owner of a motor vehicle does not reside in the Commonwealth,
13 the motor vehicle shall be registered with the county clerk of the county in which
14 the motor vehicle is principally operated. If the owner of a motor vehicle is other
15 than an individual and resides in the Commonwealth, the motor vehicle shall be
16 registered with the county clerk of either county. The application when presented to
17 the county clerk for registration shall be accompanied by:
18 (a) A bill of sale and a manufacturer's certificate of origin if the application is for
19 the registration of a new motor vehicle;
20 (b) The owner's registration receipt, if the motor vehicle was last registered in this
21 state;
22 (c) A bill of sale and the previous registration receipt, if last registered in another
23 state where the law of that state does not require the owner of a motor vehicle
24 to obtain a certificate of title or ownership;
25 (d) A certificate of title, if last registered in another state where the law of that
26 state requires the owner of a motor vehicle to obtain a certificate of title or
27 ownership;
